I'm sure many people that were kind enough to donate their time to try and help me drop Naggy last night have ideas about where we goofed on both attempts.<br>
<br>
Since I spent most of the time zoning (being banished and gating back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), I did not see a lot of what went down. However, there are a few things I did notice, realize, or deduce via the outcome...<br>
<br>
1. No 52- Enchanter. That's right, not a single Enchanter was there that was 52 or under. What's that mean? No Tashania. As we all know, this has a trickle down affect much like an avalanche. This also means we had no Rune, or at least, no chain runing.<br>
<br>
2. No Slow. With no Enchanter to Tash, Shamans could not get a slow to stick. Non-slowed Nagafen makes frozen baby Belmonte cry.<br>
<br>
3. Mis-timed healing. I do want to thank all the clerics that attended, and I don't want to put anyone on the defensive, but I received several tells last night from melee that said that they were not getting heals on time, or at all. We can't kill Nagafen if all our melees are dead. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
4. Mis-used healing. This is my fault. After thinking about it last night - I didn't get much sleep last night - I asked the group Clerics to use the wrong heal. The group clerics should have stuck to Word of Healing, casting as necessary (read: not necessarily spamming). It's all well and good that the clerics kept their groups main tank alive, but by doing that, sacrificed the remaining 5 members, including themselves. A group heal every Dragon Roar or two woulda kept <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> everyone</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> alive... not just the group's main tank.<br>
<br>
5. Buffing. This seems to be the proverbial thorn in a raid leader's side. Buffing can get confused so badly that they start wearing off. People start complaining that buffs are fading/faded, adding to the mess and confusion. It's a fun experience! /sarc off. Next time, I will have the buffing organized and in an order that will expedite the process and keep people happy.<br>
<br>
6. Resist Gear. I think a lot of people didn't have sufficient FR/MR gear, thus took a heap of AoE damage and were Feared a lot. For everyone <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> except</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the MA and maybe SA, the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> important stats for you are your HPs, FR, and MR. AC means squat, WIS and INT, to an extent, mean squat. You can't melee/nuke/heal if you're dead (from the AoE).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --WHAT WENT RIGHT--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1. The experiment was a complete success. A 53+ Cleric can in fact CHeal the MA, get banished to LS and gate back to the buff room to rinse and repeat as necessary!<br>
<br>
2. /sigh. I don't think there <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a 2. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
(damn, that's a pretty short list, neh?)<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
Now, as for what sort of strategy I've come up with, with the knowledge I've gained from last night's escapades...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --GROUPS--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1.<br>
-Warrior (MA)<br>
-melee<br>
