<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --BUFFING (spell - duration)--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1. Junk Buffs<br>
-Call of Summer&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (GRC - DRU) - 36<br>
-Talisman of Jacinth (GRD - SHM) - 36<br>
-Talisman of Shadoo (GRP - SHM) - 36<br>
<br>
2. Cleric Buffs<br>
-Aegolism - 150<br>
-Heroic Bond - 72<br>
-Symbol or Pinzarn - 45<br>
<br>
3. Shaman Buffs<br>
-Agility - 63<br>
-Dexterity - 63<br>
-Strength - 63<br>
<br>
4. Enchanter Buffs<br>
-Group Resist Magic - 36<br>
-Clarity/2 - 27/35<br>
-Celerity/Swift like the Wind - 16/16<br>
-Rune V/VI (MA and SA only) - N/A<br>
<br>
5. Druid Buffs<br>
-Call of Winter&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - 36<br>
-Pack Chloroplast - 8<br>
<br>
6. Magician Buffs<br>
-Boon of Immolation - 6<br>
-Fire Resist Shoulders - N/A<br>
<br>
Even though it is considered &quot;outdated&quot; with the new /targetgroupbuff switch, I'm thinking maybe camping to chat isn't such a bad idea. There are still a lot of necessary buffs that have no group equivalent, which just means more time and mana (time and mana being fairly synonymous in this respect).<br>
<br>
Throwing buffs on groups one at a time, and sending them to chat when finished would make sure that all groups had all buffs, which wouldn't fade out 5 seconds before engaging Nagafen.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --BATTLE--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1. MA charges in on Nagafen, soloing him in his lair.<br>
2. 53+ Cleric01 Complete heals MA (is banished to Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
3. Tashania on Nagafen. (Enchanters then chain Rune MA)<br>
4. Groups 1 and 2 engage Nagafen.<br>
5. Slow on Nagafen.<br>
6. 53+ Cleric02 Complete heals MA (is banished to Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
7. Groups 3 and 4 engage Nagafen<br>
8. 53+ Cleric03 Complete Heals MA (is banished to Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
9. Repeat 53+ Cleric rotation as necessary.<br>
10. At &quot;Lord&quot;, casters engage and burn Nagafen down.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> --HEALING--</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1. 53+ Clerics CHeal MA (rotation).<br>
2. 52- Group Clerics Group Heal (Word of Healing) as necessary.<br>
<br>
This is all I can think of at the moment. I'll probably add to it during lunch~<br>
<br>
I just want to again thank <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all of you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> who helped last night. I know the end was undesirable, but the effort and willingness to dedicate that insane amount of time losing XP instead of gaining it elsewhere means a lot. To me at least. The the entire Cleric community, I'm sure.<br>
<br>
For those that were there, your thoughts? <p><i>
