<br>
- AE heals are not so good. They use a ton of mana, and with fear effects half of each group is likely to be out of range. Have it memorized just in case, but concentrate on direct heals.<br>
<br>
- camp outs are always a good idea on naggy/vox runs.<br>
<br>
- healers, work together by targeting Nagafen and /assisting him to see who he is hitting. Keeping that person alive should be your first priority. Paladins, use your LoH - on the warriors - and remember you are as much a healer as melee in this kind of fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C5C5BA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ugoldenblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goldenblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Fire Beetles<br> The TRUE Red-headed Stepchild </span><br>  Posts: 817<br> <font color=#122950>(12/21/01 10:43:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4168.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://roguewiz.itgo.com/fire.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=72></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen last night (12-20-01)</span><hr size=1> Actually...you had 1 wizard.  1 Wizard on a Naggy raid 90% of the time=failure <p><table BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 COLS=1 WIDTH="38%" BACKGROUND="http://legacy.slicked.net/test.JPG" >
