Waves:<br>
For the most part, waves are done for aggro management, so the right people have aggro, and the wrong people don't. I think that's pretty much it. There's also a trade-off with damage taken to damage done, not sure if it's 'equal' or lopsided, haven't been to enough Naggy raids to test it.<br>
 <br>
Nuking<br>
Caster's are extremely low on HPs. Were they to go in a blazing from the get go, get summoned, and die...their chances of getting back in and landing another nuke are slim to none. Considering they'd be going back in naked (read: no AC, no WIS/INT, no resists) the chances are they'd be dead before their DragonNuke01 got off.<br>
<br>
Shaman<br>
Karaln tried to slow Nagafen, but since there was no Tash or Malo on Naggy, it didnt stick.<br>
<br>
-Avezes-<br>
Only problem with just healing those 4 tanks.. is all the rest die, which = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> far</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> less damage.<br>
<br>
The 52- group Clerics should only be healing AoE damage, since the banish Clerics will be CHealing the MA, who should have aggro the entire time and be the only one taking melee damage.<br>
<br>
Since AoE damage should hit all the group members fairly equally - barring resists n such - it makes more sense to use an AoE heal.<br>
<br>
Dragon Roar does 500 damage.<br>
Word of Healing does 500-600 healing.<br>
<br>
Tit for tat, ya know?<br>
<br>
-Sielle- <br>
