</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#B8C0C7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukrieldarkbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kriel Darkbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Torvonnite</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#122950>(12/21/01 11:07:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4168.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen last night (12-20-01)</span><hr size=1> $0.02 from someone who's done Naggy and Vox too many times (take it or ignore it as you see fit):<br>
<br>
&gt;1. No 52- Enchanter. That's right, not a single Enchanter &gt;was there that was 52 or under. What's that mean? No &gt;Tashania. As we all know, this has a trickle down affect &gt;much like an avalanche. This also means we had no Rune, or &gt;at least, no chain runing.<br>
<br>
On most of the Vox/Naggy raids I've been on (hereafter referred to as dragon raids), The dragon has not been slowed. It's WONDERFUL if it happens, but it's quite rare. If you're counting on it, you're in trouble. The dragon usually resists every cast, Tashania or no Tashania. I don't know if I've ever seen anyone bother chain-runing, but it certainly couldn't hurt. What else is the sacrificial enchanter going to do after Tash anyway?<br>
<br>
&gt;2. No Slow. With no Enchanter to Tash, Shamans could not &gt;get a slow to stick. Non-slowed Nagafen makes frozen baby &gt;Belmonte cry.<br>
<br>
Like I said before, the dragons usually resist all the slows, Tash or no Tash. It's great if you can slow him - if he's slowed and you still lose your raid had SERIOUS issues. But usually he will NOT be slowed no matter what. So don't make it a critical part of your strategy. <br>
<br>
&gt;3. Mis-timed healing. I do want to thank all the clerics that &gt;attended, and I don't want to put anyone on the defensive, &gt;but I received several tells last night from melee that said &gt;that they were not getting heals on time, or at all. We can't &gt;kill Nagafen if all our melees are dead.  <br>
<br>
That can certainly be a problem. CH in particular is often too slow if someone has serious aggro. But it could be much more a resist gear issue than a healing timing issue. If the cleric is feared he's not healing. If the melee is sucking up full damage from every AE he's not WORTH healing - the cleric doesn't have enough mana if resists are too low. It's hard to get people with good resist gear since they're mostly inexperienced, but try to emphasize it as much as you can. <br>
<br>
&gt;4. Mis-used healing. This is my fault. After thinking about it &gt;last night - I didn't get much sleep last night - I asked the &gt;group Clerics to use the wrong heal. The group clerics &gt;should have stuck to Word of Healing, casting as necessary &gt;(read: not necessarily spamming). It's all well and good that &gt;the clerics kept their groups main tank alive, but by doing &gt;that, sacrificed the remaining 5 members, including &gt;themselves. A group heal every Dragon Roar or two woulda &gt;kept everyone alive... not just the group's main tank.<br>
<br>
You can try it that way if you want, but it's very risky. The cleric MUST have excellent resist gear to use that strategy - or he's going to be feared or dead himself. Secondly, it generates WAY more aggro than tossing around Celestial Healing. Most of the clerics I've seen try to use group heals, especially repeated casts of them, ended up tanking (ie dead). Again it could be a level /resist gear issue - a 50-52 melee with adequate resists should only need a Celestial healing or two to survive the first, unless they end up tanking. Bards help a lot with making that happen. <br>
<br>
&gt;5. Buffing. This seems to be the proverbial thorn in a raid &gt;leader's side. Buffing can get confused so badly that they &gt;start wearing off. People start complaining that buffs are &gt;fading/faded, adding to the mess and confusion. It's a fun &gt;experience! /sarc off. Next time, I will have the buffing &gt;organized and in an order that will expedite the process and &gt;keep people happy.<br>
<br>
God I hated buffing for those things. I'd definitely have people camp to chat when they are fully buffed - why not? Try to get buffing as organized as possible, and done as fast as possible. But if people are going to be just sitting around waiting for buffing to finish, they can do it in chat as easily as in the buff hall - and without their buff timers running. <br>
<br>
&gt;6. Resist Gear. I think a lot of people didn't have sufficient &gt;FR/MR gear, thus took a heap of AoE damage and were &gt;Feared a lot. For everyone except the MA and maybe SA, &gt;the only important stats for you are your HPs, FR, and MR. &gt;AC means squat, WIS and INT, to an extent, mean squat. &gt;You can't melee/nuke/heal if you're dead (from the AoE).<br>
<br>
Resists are certainly critical. It's so hard to get good resist gear on everyone when you're scrambling for people in the first place. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&gt;--WHAT WENT RIGHT--<br>
&gt;1. The experiment was a complete success. A 53+ Cleric can &gt;in fact CHeal the MA, get banished to LS and gate back to &gt;the buff room to rinse and repeat as necessary!<br>
<br>
How long does this take? If there's time to do it more than once or maybe twice I suspect the raid is taking too long and won't win. <br>
<br>
&gt;--BATTLE--<br>
&gt;1. MA charges in on Nagafen, soloing him in his lair.<br>
&gt;2. 53+ Cleric01 Complete heals MA (is banished to &gt;Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
&gt;3. Tashania on Nagafen. (Enchanters then chain Rune MA)<br>
&gt;4. Groups 1 and 2 engage Nagafen.<br>
&gt;5. Slow on Nagafen.<br>
&gt;6. 53+ Cleric02 Complete heals MA (is banished to &gt;Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
&gt;7. Groups 3 and 4 engage Nagafen<br>
&gt;8. 53+ Cleric03 Complete Heals MA (is banished to &gt;Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
&gt;9. Repeat 53+ Cleric rotation as necessary.<br>
&gt;10. At &quot;Lord&quot;, casters engage and burn Nagafen down.<br>
<br>
Why so many waves? I've seen many raid leaders have the melee groups go in in waves like that. But other than only sending in one group for the initial rush to position the dragon and suck up the first AE, why hold the melee's back? What is actually gained? <br>
<br>
Also, I'd send in the casters a lot sooner than &quot;Lord&quot;. A good wizard can do several thousand damage with Ice Comet - the tanks need to get some solid aggro first, but as soon as they do, unleash any 49+ wizards you have. I remember one Naggy raid Tuvus did 5k+ damage (L 51 wiz) - If you wait until &quot;Lord&quot;, Naggy only has that many hp left before you even call for the nukes. <br>
<br>
&gt;--HEALING--<br>
&gt;1. 53+ Clerics CHeal MA (rotation).<br>
&gt;2. 52- Group Clerics Group Heal (Word of Healing) as &gt;necessary.<br>
<br>
I realize it's natural for you to focus on what a 53+ cleric can do to help, but, honestly, if you're needed the raid has serious problems. You will be zoning in and out, only get off a couple heals - and you won't be there when one is really needed. <br>
<br>
I like your suggested group makeups, with one suggestion: If you have enough clerics to at ALL be able to manage it, I'd suggest a group like this:<br>
<br>
3 L 50-52 warriors, L 50-52 bard, two L 50-52 clerics. If these people all have good resists (pick ones who do), the group is extremely tough. At those levels, the warriors don't even have to max out on resist gear, since the bard will likely be there for resists (they should still have at least some of the better resist gear on - froggy crowns and such). The beauty of this group is that the dragon has an extremely hard time killing anyone in the group - a cleric with aggro can DA or be healed by the other cleric, one can heal the group while the other heals the main tank. I've been in groups like this on dragon raids where the dragon really couldn't kill anyone in the group, even if it wasn't slowed. Leave a caster or misc melee group without a cleric to form a group like this, if you have to. If they have bad resist gear they're not worth a cleric anyway. <br>
<br>
I hope there's something you find useful in that mess. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kriel<br>
