For the most part, waves are done for aggro management, so the right people have aggro, and the wrong people don't. I think that's pretty much it. There's also a trade-off with damage taken to damage done, not sure if it's 'equal' or lopsided, haven't been to enough Naggy raids to test it.  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hmm, it might be worth something for the aggro management reason, but it most definitely is NOT as far as a damage done/taken tradeoff. Think about it this way: what's a better tradeoff: 12 people attacking Nag, or 24? With 12, you have 12 hitting him, and twelve taking his AE plus one taking his melee. With 24, you have 24 hitting him, with 24 taking his AE and one taking his melee. <br>
<br>
More people give you the advantage - more people are doing damage to him, but he's still only doing his melee damage to one person. Relatively speaking, Naggy is doing AE + melee/(number of people fighting him) in average damage to each person. The more people in the fight, the less damage he is doing compared to the damage he is taking. If not, get rid of some of the low level/low resist people who don't belong in the fight. Or just don't heal them and be glad of the 500 or so damage they do before getting killed. <br>
<br>
Kriel<br>
