The addition of 53+ clerics to the mix was...in theory...a fail safe. It didnt work out that way unfortunately.<br>
<br>
On the two dragon raids I was on when 52- (1 Vox, 1 Nagafen), I was cleric in group 1. It was my job to CHeal the MA. The second I did, bam! summoned and wiped out in short order.<br>
<br>
The addition of the 53+ clerics is to get Cheals on the MA, and not sacrifice any clerics that can actually engage him. I thought this alone, 3 un-touchable Cheals, would help the MA gain/maintain aggro, and keep the raid clerics alive. I think the AoE group heals will work since, by the time they are cast, the MA has built up sufficient hate (he will have soloed Nagafen for a good 10-15 seconds) for Nagafen to disregard anyone else.<br>
<br>
For some unknown reason(s), it didn't work out as planned. It had Careden, Cresendia, and myself stupified as to how and why it wasn't working like a charm. /sigh<br>
<br>
That 10-step process was just an initial thought running through my head.. I'm sure I'll tweak and condense it. Maybe like...<br>
<br>
1. MA charges in on Nagafen, soloing him in his lair.<br>
2. 53+ Cleric01 Complete heals MA (is banished to Lavastorm, gates back to buff room)<br>
3. Tashania on Nagafen. (Enchanters then chain Rune MA)<br>
4. Slow Nagafen<br>
5. Groups 1, 2, 3, and 4 (melee) engage Nagafen.<br>
6. Repeat 53+ Cleric rotation as necessary.<br>
7. At &quot;Lord Na&quot; (that's about 50% neh?), casters engage and burn Nagafen down.<br>
<br>
This would suck it down to three waves (MA for intitial aggro, melees, casters)... might take some of the confusion out.<br>
<br>
-Kakarat-<br>
