<br>
Next my sexy De darling.. give me a tell... I was just camping a dumb dagger... could have easily come down to help buff up and even tried to land a slow on Ole Naggy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But seriously... when it come to buffing... have each group that has been finished being buffed camp out to a room! Then when everyone is done.. have them come back in for the fight. That way the buffs are still fresh til they die! Ok... Im not entirely sure that was clear so Ill list what was done on the last Naggy raid I was a participant. (Twas a successfull raid too!)<br>
<br>
1) Groups made in buff room<br>
<br>
2) Buffers placed in separate locations for buffing of groups.<br>
<br>
3) Call in Group #1 for buffs i.e. they go to shaman(s) first...<br>
<br>
When they are done getting them...<br>
<br>
4) Call in Group #2 for buffs from first buffer and send Group #1 to second buffer i.e. Cleric(s) &amp;/or Druid(s)<br>
<br>
When they are done...<br>
<br>
5) Call in Group #3 for buff from first buffer Group #2 goes to 2nd buffer Group #1 goes to 3rd buffer i.e. mage(s) &amp;/or echanter(s)<br>
<br>
Now you just wash/rinse/repeat for the remaining groups til everyone that needs to be buffed is done. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
OH and once EACH group is done being buffed HAVE THEM CAMP and go to a chat room to wait for fight. This way buffs are fresh still everyone has them and the fight can have a better chance of working right!<br>
<br>
